reviewText: I had this DVD for a few days now and I have finally workout to it tonight. I love this DVD. The 45 minutes flew by. I catch on to things quick and this DVD was no different. I recommend this DVD to any other Core Rhythms fan. This is a must have DVD. I know that if I keep up with doing this DVD along with my other DVDs and eating right. I will see a change in my body.

reviewText: This looks easier than it is and wow does it work.  Great workout.  I liked the option to have them facing away from you so you could follow easier; i.e. when they are on their left foot (facing forward) you are using your right foot, which can make it hard to follow.  With this option, when they are facing away from you , their right foot is you right foot.  Hope this doesn't confuse you.  It's as if you are in back of them following them.

reviewText: first let me say that core rhythms can be a very good workout. i love the way they utalize the main problem areas that a women faces. her abs, hips, and whole lower body. why have i giving it a low rating? reviewText: I just got done with this workout and had to write a review.  It was so much fun, the moves had such toning purpose, the women are cheerful - I loved every second.  If you give it everything you got you will sweat and have fun.  I am someone who thought the Zumba DVDs were so boring and uneffective.  Get this DVD!
